    <!--
      SharedLib .cpp files compiled INTO RcMods.dll.

      SharedLib is Utility-only (no .lib output) — the .cpp files transitively
      #include game-specific headers (Common.h, Lib_Forward.h, the generated
      SDK), so each consumer must compile them against its own SDK in-place.
      Removing these entries causes "unresolved external symbol" linker errors
      for everything in SharedLib.

      Excluded for RC:
        - Lib_Json.cpp — depends on DRG-specific JSON_* SDK headers
          (JSONType_structs.hpp, JSON_classes.hpp, JSONValue_classes.hpp,
          JSON_parameters.hpp); RogueCore exposes a different / no JSON
          binding. Port when RC needs blueprint JSON access.

      Lib_ObjectFactory.cpp IS compiled for RC but currently logs and
      no-ops at runtime — fill in RcMods/GameOffsets.h with RC's
      SCO_Internal RVA or call-site signature to enable NewObject<T>().
    -->
